            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20church%20in%20the%20wilderness%20modeled%20the%20biblical%20pattern%20of%20oversight.%20Leaders%20of%20tens%2C%20fifties%2C%20hundreds%2C%20and%20thousands%20were%20selected%20to%20care%20for%20the%20basic%20needs%20of%20the%20people%20and%20to%20settle%20their%20disputes.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Moses%20had%20to%20review%20only%20the%20most%20difficult%20cases%20and%20policies.%20His%20primary%20job%20was%20to%20commune%20with%20God%20and%20to%20teach%20the%20Word.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20apostles%20discovered%20this%20principle%20in%20the%20selection%20of%20deacons%2C%20which%20freed%20them%20to%20use%20their%20time%20%22in%20prayer%20and%20preaching%20and%20teaching%20the%20word%22%20(Acts%206%3A4).%20The%20early%20church%20not%20only%20met%20daily%20in%20the%20temple%20but%20also%20gathered%20%22in%20homes%20for%20the%20Lord's%20Supper%2C%20and%20shared%20their%20meals%20with%20great%20joy%20and%20generosity%20(Acts%202%3A46).%20Apostles%2C%20deacons%2C%20and%20church%20members%20all%20helped%20carry%20the%20load%20of%20the%20growing%20congregation.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBurned-out%20pastors%20and%20leaders%20are%20a%20testimony%20to%20the%20huge%20toll%20of%20counseling%2C%20visiting%2C%20and%20arbitrating%20required%20in%20the%20church%20today.%20In%20actuality%2C%20the%20pastor%20is%20not%20called%20to%20do%20all%20ministry%2C%20but%20he%20is%20%22to%20equip%20God's%20people%20to%20do%20his%20work%20and%20build%20up%20the%20church%22%20(Ephesians%204%3A12).%20Pastors%2C%20bring%20them%20in%2C%20build%20them%20up%2C%20release%20their%20gifts%2C%20and%20send%20them%20out.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20you%20will%20be%20able%20to%20endure%20as%20Moses%20did.%20%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Exodus.17:8-19:15",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EExodus%2017%3A8-19%3A15%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_8%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EIsrael%20Defeats%20the%20Amalekites%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EWhile%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20were%20still%20at%20Rephidim%2C%20the%20warriors%20of%20Amalek%20attacked%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_9%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20commanded%20Joshua%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BChoose%20some%20men%20to%20go%20out%20and%20fight%20the%20army%20of%20Amalek%20for%20us.%20Tomorrow%2C%20I%20will%20stand%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20hill%2C%20holding%20the%20staff%20of%20God%20in%20my%20hand.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_10%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Joshua%20did%20what%20Moses%20had%20commanded%20and%20fought%20the%20army%20of%20Amalek.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Moses%2C%20Aaron%2C%20and%20Hur%20climbed%20to%20the%20top%20of%20a%20nearby%20hill.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_11%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20long%20as%20Moses%20held%20up%20the%20staff%20in%20his%20hand%2C%20the%20Israelites%20had%20the%20advantage.%20But%20whenever%20he%20dropped%20his%20hand%2C%20the%20Amalekites%20gained%20the%20advantage.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_12%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%26%23x2019%3B%20arms%20soon%20became%20so%20tired%20he%20could%20no%20longer%20hold%20them%20up.%20So%20Aaron%20and%20Hur%20found%20a%20stone%20for%20him%20to%20sit%20on.%20Then%20they%20stood%20on%20each%20side%20of%20Moses%2C%20holding%20up%20his%20hands.%20So%20his%20hands%20held%20steady%20until%20sunset.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_13%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Joshua%20overwhelmed%20the%20army%20of%20Amalek%20in%20battle.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_14%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20the%20victory%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20instructed%20Moses%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWrite%20this%20down%20on%20a%20scroll%20as%20a%20permanent%20reminder%2C%20and%20read%20it%20aloud%20to%20Joshua%3A%20I%20will%20erase%20the%20memory%20of%20Amalek%20from%20under%20heaven.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_15%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20built%20an%20altar%20there%20and%20named%20it%20Yahweh-Nissi%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bthe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20my%20banner%26%23x201D%3B).%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_17_16%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThey%20have%20raised%20their%20fist%20against%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20throne%2C%20so%20now%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A16%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EHands%20have%20been%20lifted%20up%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%20class%3D%22tn-sc-ital%22%3ELord%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20throne%2C%20and%20now.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20be%20at%20war%20with%20Amalek%20generation%20after%20generation.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_1%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EExodus%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJethro%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Visit%20to%20Moses%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%26%23x2019%3B%20father-in-law%2C%20Jethro%2C%20the%20priest%20of%20Midian%2C%20heard%20about%20everything%20God%20had%20done%20for%20Moses%20and%20his%20people%2C%20the%20Israelites.%20He%20heard%20especially%20about%20how%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20rescued%20them%20from%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_2%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EEarlier%2C%20Moses%20had%20sent%20his%20wife%2C%20Zipporah%2C%20and%20his%20two%20sons%20back%20to%20Jethro%2C%20who%20had%20taken%20them%20in.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_3%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E(Moses%26%23x2019%3B%20first%20son%20was%20named%20Gershom%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E18%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cem%3EGershom%3C%2Fem%3E%20sounds%20like%20a%20Hebrew%20term%20that%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Ba%20foreigner%20there.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20Moses%20had%20said%20when%20the%20boy%20was%20born%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20have%20been%20a%20foreigner%20in%20a%20foreign%20land.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_4%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EHis%20second%20son%20was%20named%20Eliezer%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E18%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cem%3EEliezer%3C%2Fem%3E%20means%20%26%23x201C%3BGod%20is%20my%20helper.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20Moses%20had%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20God%20of%20my%20ancestors%20was%20my%20helper%3B%20he%20rescued%20me%20from%20the%20sword%20of%20Pharaoh.%26%23x201D%3B)%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_5%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EJethro%2C%20Moses%26%23x2019%3B%20father-in-law%2C%20now%20came%20to%20visit%20Moses%20in%20the%20wilderness.%20He%20brought%20Moses%26%23x2019%3B%20wife%20and%20two%20sons%20with%20him%2C%20and%20they%20arrived%20while%20Moses%20and%20the%20people%20were%20camped%20near%20the%20mountain%20of%20God.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_6%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EJethro%20had%20sent%20a%20message%20to%20Moses%2C%20saying%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%2C%20Jethro%2C%20your%20father-in-law%2C%20am%20coming%20to%20see%20you%20with%20your%20wife%20and%20your%20two%20sons.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_7%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Moses%20went%20out%20to%20meet%20his%20father-in-law.%20He%20bowed%20low%20and%20kissed%20him.%20They%20asked%20about%20each%20other%26%23x2019%3Bs%20welfare%20and%20then%20went%20into%20Moses%26%23x2019%3B%20tent.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_8%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20told%20his%20father-in-law%20everything%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20done%20to%20Pharaoh%20and%20Egypt%20on%20behalf%20of%20Israel.%20He%20also%20told%20about%20all%20the%20hardships%20they%20had%20experienced%20along%20the%20way%20and%20how%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20rescued%20his%20people%20from%20all%20their%20troubles.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_9%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EJethro%20was%20delighted%20when%20he%20heard%20about%20all%20the%20good%20things%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20done%20for%20Israel%20as%20he%20rescued%20them%20from%20the%20hand%20of%20the%20Egyptians.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_10%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BPraise%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Jethro%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bfor%20he%20has%20rescued%20you%20from%20the%20Egyptians%20and%20from%20Pharaoh.%20Yes%2C%20he%20has%20rescued%20Israel%20from%20the%20powerful%20hand%20of%20Egypt!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_11%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20know%20now%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20greater%20than%20all%20other%20gods%2C%20because%20he%20rescued%20his%20people%20from%20the%20oppression%20of%20the%20proud%20Egyptians.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_12%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jethro%2C%20Moses%26%23x2019%3B%20father-in-law%2C%20brought%20a%20burnt%20offering%20and%20sacrifices%20to%20God.%20Aaron%20and%20all%20the%20elders%20of%20Israel%20came%20out%20and%20joined%20him%20in%20a%20sacrificial%20meal%20in%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_13%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJethro%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Wise%20Advice%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20Moses%20took%20his%20seat%20to%20hear%20the%20people%26%23x2019%3Bs%20disputes%20against%20each%20other.%20They%20waited%20before%20him%20from%20morning%20till%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_14%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Moses%26%23x2019%3B%20father-in-law%20saw%20all%20that%20Moses%20was%20doing%20for%20the%20people%2C%20he%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20are%20you%20really%20accomplishing%20here%3F%20Why%20are%20you%20trying%20to%20do%20all%20this%20alone%20while%20everyone%20stands%20around%20you%20from%20morning%20till%20evening%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_15%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BBecause%20the%20people%20come%20to%20me%20to%20get%20a%20ruling%20from%20God.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_16%22%20bk%3D%22exod%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20a%20dispute%20arises%2C%20they%20come%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20am%20the%20one%20who%20settles%20the%20case%20between%20the%20quarreling%20parties.%20I%20inform%20the%20people%20of%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20decrees%20and%20give%20them%20his%20instructions.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22exod_18_17%22%20bk%3D%22